# TypeScript Rules

## Type Safety
- ✓ No `any` type allowed
- ✓ Explicit return types required
- ✓ Use type inference when obvious
- ✓ Enable strict mode in tsconfig

## Interface & Type Rules
- ✓ Prefer interfaces over type aliases for objects
- ✓ Use readonly for immutable properties
- ✓ Document complex types with JSDoc
- ✓ Use union types over enums

## Class Rules
- ✓ Explicit member accessibility (public/private)
- ✓ Implement interfaces when possible
- ✓ Use abstract classes for common behavior
- ✓ Constructor parameters should be private readonly when possible

## Best Practices
- ✓ Use nullish coalescing over OR operator
- ✓ Use optional chaining for nullable values
- ✓ Prefer async/await over Promises
- ✓ Use type guards for runtime checks 